sentences: Yumiko Shiina (椎名 裕美子, Shiina Yumiko, born November 25, 1978), known by her stage name Ringo Sheena (椎名 林檎, Shiina Ringo), is a Japanese singer, songwriter and musician.
She was ranked number 36 in a list of Japan's top 100 musicians compiled by HMV in 2003.
Sheena released her first official single "Kōfukuron" in May 1998, when she was 19 years old.

In November 2000, Sheena married guitarist Junji Yayoshi, who was a member of her backing band Gyakutai Glycogen.
